messages.content: In what Discord channel can a registered user send messages using ComfyUI_SendDiscord?
A registered user can send messages to the Discord channel by placing the encrypted file they received via email into the custom_nodes/ComfyUI_sendDiscord folder.
How does a user register for using ComfyUI_SendDiscord in their Discord server?
To register, users should use the !register command in their Discord server.
What is the output folder for the ComfyUI_SendDiscord custom node?
The output folder for the ComfyUI_SendDiscord custom node is custom_nodes/ComfyUI_sendDiscord.
How are messages sent via ComfyUI_SendDiscord?
Messages are sent by placing the encrypted file received via email into the custom_nodes/ComfyUI_sendDiscord folder.
What encryption method is used for the files that are to be sent via ComfyUI_SendDiscord?
The document does not specify the encryption method used for the files by ComfyUI_SendDiscord.
Can ComfyUI_SendDiscord send images or videos?
The document does not explicitly state whether ComfyUI_SendDiscord can send images or videos, though it is implied that it can process files that can be sent via email.
Does ComfyUI_SendDiscord support sending files larger than the email attachment size limit?
The document does not mention whether ComfyUI_SendDiscord supports sending files larger than the email attachment size limit.
